  database on the Swimmers page.
</p>
<br>

<h4>Why do swimmers need a phone number to be checked in?</h4>
<p>
  Swimmers need a valid ten-digit phone number stored in order to be checked in for safety reasons. If for some reason not all swimmers are accounted for at the end of a session
  you can simply click CALL on the CHECK OUT page to call the swimmer directly and make sure they have exited the water safely. This usually happens because a swimmer did not
  get checked out properly at the end of their swim.
</p>
<br>

<h4>What if a swimmer needs to update their information?</h4>
<p>
  <b>Check In Page</b></br>
  On the Check In page, admins can click on the name of a swimmer to change their phone number, first name, or last name, then click Save. Non-admin monitors are not allowed
  to update swimmer information.

  <br><br>
  <b>Swimmers Page (admin only)</b></br>
  On the Swimmers page, admins can click on the name of a swimmer or click EDIT to change their phone number, first name, or last name, then click Save. Non-admin monitors are not allowed
  to view the Swimmers page or update swimmer information.
</p>
<br>

<h4>How do I give access to other monitors to log in?</h4>
<p>
  Only admin monitors can create other monitor logins. Visit the MONITORS page, then click ADD MONITOR to create a login for another monitor. Once added, you can add or remove admin privileges from them as well.
</p>
<br>

